a.What is Shared Preferences?

Ans. Android provids many ways of storing application data.One 
of its way is called Shared Preferences.Shared Preferences allows to save and 
retrieve data in the form of key value pair.


b.What values can be saved in SharedPreferences?
Ans. Shared Preferences stores priavte primitive persistent data(ex.user 
specific settings)in a key value pair.For example data could be End Point 
URL,Security Access Token and certain user prefernces like color,tiltle,language 
etc.Data is saved when application closes and brought back when application opens again.

